---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Legislative Changes | Policy"
  description="Stay informed about recent and upcoming legislative changes affecting the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Understand how these changes may impact your benefits and rights.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Legislative Changes to AFCS</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is subject to legislative changes that can affect eligibility, compensation levels, and claim processes. This page outlines recent and upcoming legislative changes and their potential impact on veterans and service personnel.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Recent Legislative Changes</h2>
        <p>Key changes implemented in the past few years:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>2021: Expansion of mental health coverage under AFCS</li>
          <li>2020: Introduction of new tariffs for specific injuries</li>
          <li>2019: Changes to time limits for certain types of claims</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Upcoming Legislative Proposals</h2>
        <p>Potential changes under consideration:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review of compensation levels for long-term care needs</li>
          <li>Proposed adjustments to the appeals process</li>
          <li>Potential expansion of eligibility criteria for reservists</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Impact on Existing Claims</h2>
        <p>How legislative changes affect current claimants:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Retroactive application of certain beneficial changes</li>
          <li>Transition periods for implementing new regulations</li>
          <li>Options for claim reassessment under new criteria</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Parliamentary Scrutiny</h2>
        <p>The role of Parliament in shaping AFCS legislation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Select Committee inquiries into veteran support</li>
          <li>Debates on proposed amendments to AFCS regulations</li>
          <li>Input from veteran organisations in the legislative process</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">International Influences</h2>
        <p>How international developments affect UK legislation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Alignment with NATO standards on veteran support</li>
          <li>Incorporation of best practices from allied nations</li>
          <li>Adaptation to changing nature of military operations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Staying Informed</h2>
        <p>Ways to keep up-to-date with legislative changes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Regular updates on the official AFCS website</li>
          <li>Notifications through veteran support organisations</li>
          <li>Consultation opportunities for proposed changes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/policy/government-policies" class="text-decoration-none">Government Policies</a></li>
              <li><a href="/policy/legal-precedents" class="text-decoration-none">Legal Precedents</a></li>
              <li><a href="/eligibility" class="text-decoration-none">Eligibility Criteria</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Legislative Updates</h3>
            <p>Subscribe to our newsletter for the latest information on AFCS legislative changes.</p>
            <a href="/newsletter-signup" class="btn btn-primary">Subscribe Now</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
